dismissalText.commentary: Fakhar Zaman c Udana b de Silva 54 (65b 6x4 1x6) SR: 83.07

dismissalComment.html: taken at mid-off! Hasaranga gets his revenge! Tosses this one fuller and closer to Fakhar's swing. He hit him wide of mid-off last over when there was more width. This time he's forced to drive from inside the line and he ends up getting it off the low part of the outside half. Bat swivels in his hands and this floats seductively to Udana's right. He follows the path and puts something of a slow-mo dive to grab onto a well-judged catch

dismissalText.commentary: Haris Sohail run out (†Samarawickrama/Pradeep) 40 (48b 1x4 0x6) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: mix up and Haris Sohail has to go!. This was a length ball outside off, Babar tried to flick, it took an inside edge and flicked his pad and rolled away towards slip. Sohail wanted a single and was charging down the track, Babar was never interested and/or aware of what his partner was doing till he belatedly sent him back. The throw was relayed to the bowler and he took out the stumps from a yard away with Sohail well short

dismissalComment.html: got him? Yes! A faint edge! It's not to be for Shehan Jayasuriya. He's looking at the heavens in despair. What a knock. Just not enough to best Pakistan's best bowler on the night. Length all angled into the corridor. Opens the face and wants to run this down to third man but gets a faint edge that carries to the keeper. A standing ovation as he goes off. He's doubled his ODI tally today with his first fifty. Won't forget this for a long time

dismissalText.commentary: Dasun Shanaka c Fakhar Zaman b Shadab Khan 68 (80b 6x4 2x6) SR: 85

dismissalComment.html: finds deep midwicket! In three balls, a potential miracle has been seriously dented. That's a terrible delivery if you ask anyone, including the bowler himself. Very short on off stump. Backs away and looks to pull this over the midwicket boundary. It comes off the toe-end and Fakhar runs in, lunges and slides with grace as he holds on to this. Shanaka kept the scoring rate ticking early on and barely did anything wrong this evening. But he won't be there at the end for Sri Lanka either

commentPostTextItems.html: 11:28pm And that is all from us tonight! Thanks for joining us and don't forget to keep an eye out for the post match stuff, starting with Andrew Fidel Fernando's match report. Good night and see you soon.

Sarfraz Ahmed: We have to improve our lines and lengths in the middle overs. The way we batted, the score was good. The ball wasn't coming on, our batsmen did well. We'll try to give everyone a chance through this series, even the guys on our bench are first priority players for us.

Lahiru Thirimanne: It was a great effort by Shehan and Dasun. They showed us how to bat in these conditions. Disappointed how we handled the first ten overs, it was not good enough. They bowled pretty well, but overall we could have kept them to below 300. Our bowlers did well in small phases, but later stages they've given some extra runs. Today, Shehan took the chance and batted really well. It's a great opportunity, the youngsters should make the most of it.

Usman Shinwari: I've come in after 5-6 months. It was a comeback of a sorts. I put in my everything. It was a slow wicket, but I stuck to my plan. [On favouring Sri Lanka, who he's taken two five-wicket hauls against] They hit me all over the park on my debut, I'm just avenging myself!
Usman Shinwari is the Man of the Match

Fahad Nasim: "Win was expected but good fight from Srilanka. Shadab khan's length and flight is a good thing in long term, he's playing first class and bowling a lot of overs hence this change in trajectory. I'll take this bashing of him throughout the series if he can develop his test bowling skills for Australia tour."

Sheikh: "#CricketComesHome in a style! *-* Congratulations Pakistan on this victory. And srilanka too for their fighting spirit "

Khalid: "Shinwari should be MoM. Great Comeback performance."

11:10pm A huge win in the end. Pakistan let the game for a long time in the second half, but they were outdone by the entirety of Sri Lanka's specialist batsmen who played some terribly ordinary shots on a good batting surface. From 28 for 5, they had no business lasting even another hour. But Shehan Jayasuriya and Dasun Shanaka, two of many players on this tour trying to prove a point, took their chances. They were positive despite the damage around them. They kept tucking the ball away, maintaining a rate of five per over until suddenly upping the rate and giving Pakistan a right scare. But Usman Shinwari, the architect of the early collapse, was there in the end to drag the game back for Pakistan. A second five-for, getting Jayasuriya for 96, and stamping his name all over this chase. A good day for him. Also a good day for Babar Azam, celebrating his first Karachi ODI with his 11th ODI ton. Iftikhar at the end with a cameo too, took Pakistan past 300. An overall decent day for the hosts, floodlight frustrations notwithstanding.

dismissalText.commentary: Lahiru Thirimanne c †Sarfaraz Ahmed b Usman Shinwari 0 (3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: is there an edge? Yes there is! But they're checking if the ball carried to Sarfaraz. Soft signal is out. Short of a length and slanted in from outside off. Looks to cut well away from his body but that comes in and he gets an under-edge on it...that looks good on carrying through to Sarfaraz. Not even a close call in the end. Captain catches captain, Sri Lanka's score reflects their woeful shot selection this evening

dismissalComment.html: looks plumb on first look. Oshada has reviewed it. Lenth ball curves in from off stump. He plays the original line outside off and the ball sneaks past the inside edge in the end he's just swishing aimlessly in front of his body. There's no inside edge. And there's no chance. Hits him in front of middle, it's going on to comfortably take leg stump as well. That's the review gone. That's Oshada gone. There's not much that isn't gone at the moment for the visitors

dismissalText.commentary: Shehan Jayasuriya c †Sarfaraz Ahmed b Usman Shinwari 96 (109b 7x4 1x6) SR: 88.07

dismissalComment.html: got him? Yes! A faint edge! It's not to be for Shehan Jayasuriya. He's looking at the heavens in despair. What a knock. Just not enough to best Pakistan's best bowler on the night. Length all angled into the corridor. Opens the face and wants to run this down to third man but gets a faint edge that carries to the keeper. A standing ovation as he goes off. He's doubled his ODI tally today with his first fifty. Won't forget this for a long time

dismissalText.commentary: Dasun Shanaka c Fakhar Zaman b Shadab Khan 68 (80b 6x4 2x6) SR: 85

dismissalComment.html: finds deep midwicket! In three balls, a potential miracle has been seriously dented. That's a terrible delivery if you ask anyone, including the bowler himself. Very short on off stump. Backs away and looks to pull this over the midwicket boundary. It comes off the toe-end and Fakhar runs in, lunges and slides with grace as he holds on to this. Shanaka kept the scoring rate ticking early on and barely did anything wrong this evening. But he won't be there at the end for Sri Lanka either

dismissalComment.html: and he's bluffed him comprehensively! Oh Wahab, why'd you do that to the poor No. 10. Bowls it short of a length. Kumara is fending for a bouncer because of that field change. He's trapped right in front of the stumps, on the knee flap, as this slides on from the surface. They don't have any reviews left, but Kumara doesn't look too livid about this so we could assume there's no bat on it
